                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d98">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/932.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Great
                            Britain</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Regarding the declaration of the special rights of Japan and Russia in Mongolia
                    and Manchuria, Langley says the British Government will admit such rights but
                    will at the same time affirm the principle of the open door.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reid</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
